Almgren-Chriss Optimal Execution Model
The Almgren-Chriss model is one of the most important models in optimal trade execution. It provides a mathematical framework to determine how to split a large order over time so that the total trading cost and risk are minimized.

Suppose a trader wants to sell X shares within a time horizon T.

If the trader sells too quickly:

Market impact increases
Price moves against them
If the trader sells too slowly:

Market risk increases
Price may move unfavorably

"""
